.DT
protect
Discworld player help
protect

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
protect - Protect a person.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
protect <person>
protect
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5
Makes you protect the person.  Protecting someone means that you take some
of the damage aimed at the person.  This is useful for protecting spell
casters whose spells are interrupted by combat.

If you use this command without any arguments it shows who is protecting
you and who you are protecting in the room.
.EP

.SH Example
.SI 5
> protect pinkfish
You protect pinkfish.

(Useful example isn't it?)
> protect
No one is protecting you.
Of the people in this room, you are protecting Pinkfish.
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
unprotect, defend, kill, stop.
.EP
